Waste Management Rules.text:
Congratulations #AlmitraPatel, a pioneering @environmentalist and activist who was #awarded the highest state honor  #Rajyotsava, recognizing her remarkable contributions to #wastemanagement and environmental  #conservation. At 88, she's an #inspiration, being the first Indian woman to graduate from the prestigious Massachusetts Institute of Technology 

Her groundbreaking work has had a lasting impact on waste management laws in India. Notably, her landmark Supreme Court case in 1996 led to the establishment of India's first solid waste management rules in 2000, with subsequent improvements in 2016 . This case highlighted the importance of proper waste disposal and its effects on public health and the environment. Congratulations #AlmiraPatel mam.
